***************************************************************************************************************
Operating System: 
	Ubuntu 14.04 kylin

How to install:
	1.install python2.7 including corresponding dependences(ie. scikit-learn, scipy, numpy).
	2.install Java runtime environment
	3.install essentia(http://essentia.upf.edu/documentation/installing.html) and corresponding dependences(such as FFTW, libavcodec, libavformat, libavutil, libavresample, libsamplerate, Taglib, libYAML)


How to use:
	1.assure your correct format file.
		*TrainList: data/1.wav	Rock
		*TestList: data/2.wav
	2.assure the correct place of your data.
		*data: includes all the music songs(such as 1.wav, 2.wav)
		*index: includes TrainList and TestList
	3.extract features for both TrainList and TestList.
		*commond: python src/run.py -ext index/TrainFile.list index/TestFile.list outFile.list
	4.train and classify
		*commond: python src/run.py -clf index/TranFile.list index/TestFile.list outFile.list
	5.view your result
		*outFile.list includes the prediction result, song name and label are seperated by tab.

